citation.excerpt:
A Re-implementation of Fixed-update Initialization (https://arxiv.org/abs/1901.09321). (requires Pytorch 1.0) 
Cite as: 
Hongyi Zhang, Yann N. Dauphin, Tengyu Ma. Fixup Initialization: Residual Learning Without Normalization. 7th International Conference on Learning Representations (ICLR 2019). 
The default arguments will train a ResNet-110 (https://arxiv.org/abs/1512.03385) with Fixup + Mixup (https://arxiv.org/abs/1710.09412).

description.excerpt: Top-1 accuracy for ResNet-50 at Epoch 100 with Mixup (alpha=0.7) is around 76.0%.

installation.excerpt: Transformer model with Fixup (instead of layer normalization) is available. To run the experiments, you will need to download and install the fairseq library (the provided code was tested on an earlier version: https://github.com/pytorch/fairseq/tree/5d00e8eea2644611f397d05c6c8f15083388b8b4). You can then copy the files into corresponding folders.
